COLOMBO , April 5 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Sri Lankan Foreign Minister Lakshman Kadirgamar briefed editors of local newspapers on the process that had led to the agreement between the People 's Alliance -LRB- PA -RRB- and the United National Party -LRB- UNP -RRB- on ending the ethnic conflict , according to a news release from the ministry this afternoon .
The release said the foreign minister Friday night told the editors that there was no plan at this point for talks with the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam -LRB- LTTE -RRB- .
`` The government had consistently expressed willingness to open a dialogue with the LTTE , subject to conditions including a substantial laying down of arms and an agreement to arrive at a settlement within a stipulated time frame , '' the minister said .
Kadirgamar also said the government was not contemplating mediation or facilitation by any foreign government or third party at this point .
He observed that he saw this agreement `` as significant '' and had described it `` as a step on along road . ''
He appealed to the editors `` to view this important step taken constructively and to give this new approach a chance to work in the national interest . ''
President Chandrika Kumaratunga and opposition leader Ranil Wickremesinghe Thursday agreed for the first time to cooperate on their approach to ending the ethnic conflict which has killed 55,000 people .
